HAMBURG, Germany (AP) — American Bernarda Pera will play top-seeded Anett Kontaveit in the women’s final of the Hamburg European Open after both won their semifinal matches in straight sets on Friday.The 27-year-old Pera, who secured her first WTA title in Budapest last week, advanced with a 6-2, 6-4 win over seventh-seeded Maryna Zanevska. It was Pera’s 11th straight win going back to the Budapest qualifiers after losing her previous five matches.Kontaveit beat Russian-born Anastasia Potapova 6-3, 7-5 to reach her 16th career final and her first since losing to Iga Swiatek in Doha in February.Kontaveit, who will be bidding for her seventh singles title, defeated Pera in their only previous meeting, 7-5, 6-1 in the first round at Wimbledon in June.Top-seeded Carlos Alcaraz played Karen Khachanov in the pick of the men’s quarterfinals later Friday.___More AP tennis: https://apnews.com/hub/tennis and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports